{{Not to be confused with|October 19|qq=October 19}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=十月十九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 10월 19일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar October|qq=}} '''October 19''' is the 19th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|qq=}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]] 10th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[671]] [[:en:November 25|November 25]]） – {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|大海人皇子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=}} was entrusted with state affairs by [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]], but he refused the responsibility and took monastic vows at Yoshino. * [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] 7th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1679]] [[:en:November 22|November 22]]） – The succession dispute and disturbance in [[:en:Takada Domain|Takada Domain]] was adjudicated by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=}} Tairō – [[:en:Sakai Tadakiyo|Sakai Tadayoshi]] – with the faction opposed to {{ill|Oguri Masamasa|ja|小栗美作|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oguri Masamasa|qq=}} (the hereditary retainer) being placed under another house’s custody.
== Births == * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1624]] [[:en:November 29|November 29]]） – [[:en:Sakai Tadakiyo|Sakai Tadayoshi]], an early Edo period hereditary daimyō, rōjū, and tairō (died [[1681]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1567]] [[:en:November 19|November 19]]） – [[:en:Takeda Yoshinobu|Takeda Yoshinobu]], a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}}) (born [[:en:1538|1538]]).
