== Events == * [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]] 10th year（[[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[671]] [[:en:November 25|November 25]]） – {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|ja|大海人皇子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天武天皇}} was entrusted with state affairs by [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]], but he refused the responsibility and took monastic vows at Yoshino. * [[:en:Enpō|Enpō]] 7th year（[[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1679]] [[:en:November 22|November 22]]） – The succession dispute and disturbance in [[:en:Takada Domain|Takada Domain]] was adjudicated by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|徳川幕府|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸幕府}} Tairō – [[:en:Sakai Tadakiyo|Sakai Tadayoshi]] – with the faction opposed to {{ill|Oguri Masamasa|ja|小栗美作|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oguri Masamasa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 小栗正矩}} (the hereditary retainer) being placed under another house’s custody.
== Births == * [[:en:Kan'ei|Kan'ei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1624|1624]] [[:en:November 29|November 29]]） – [[:en:Sakai Tadakiyo|Sakai Tadayoshi]], an early Edo period hereditary daimyō, rōjū, and tairō (died [[1681]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1567|1567]] [[:en:November 19|November 19]]） – [[:en:Takeda Yoshinobu|Takeda Yoshinobu]], a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|qq=}}) (born [[:en:1538|1538]]).
