'''October 19''' is the 19th day of month {{ill|October (Lunisolar)|ja|10月 (旧暦)|lt=October (Kannazuki)|1=Kannazuki|2=ja|3=10月 (旧暦)|1=Kannazuki|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/October (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kannazuki|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} the 10th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|1=Butsumetsu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10886789}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|WD=Q314802|lt=Emperor Tenji|1=Emperor Tenji}} 10th year（{{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|671|en|671|WD=Q30722|lt=671|1=671}} {{ill|November 25|en|November 25|WD=Q3020|lt=November 25|1=November 25}}） – {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|1=Emperor Tenmu|2=ja|3=天武天皇|ja|大海人皇子|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Tenmu|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天武天皇|1=Tenmu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q335181}} was entrusted with state affairs by {{ill|Emperor Tenji|en|Emperor Tenji|WD=Q314802|lt=Emperor Tenji|1=Emperor Tenji}}, but he refused the responsibility and took monastic vows at Yoshino.
* {{ill|Enpō|en|Enpō|WD=Q1145735|lt=Enpō|1=Enpō}} 7th year（{{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1679|en|1679|WD=Q7638|lt=1679|1=1679}} {{ill|November 22|en|November 22|WD=Q3025|lt=November 22|1=November 22}}） – The succession dispute and disturbance in {{ill|Takada Domain|en|Takada Domain|WD=Q839422|lt=Takada Domain|1=Takada Domain}} was adjudicated by the {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|1=Tokugawa shogunate|2=ja|3=江戸幕府|ja|徳川幕府|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokugawa shogunate|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸幕府}} Tairō – {{ill|Sakai Tadakiyo|en|Sakai Tadakiyo|WD=Q7402769|lt=Sakai Tadayoshi|1=Sakai Tadakiyo}} – with the faction opposed to {{ill|Oguri Masamasa|ja|小栗美作|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Oguri Masamasa|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 小栗正矩|1=Mimasaka Oguri|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q107647136}} (the hereditary retainer) being placed under another house’s custody.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kan'ei|en|Kan'ei|WD=Q1192913|lt=Kan'ei|1=Kan'ei}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1624|en|1624|WD=Q6821|lt=1624|1=1624}} {{ill|November 29|en|November 29|WD=Q3016|lt=November 29|1=November 29}}） – {{ill|Sakai Tadakiyo|en|Sakai Tadakiyo|WD=Q7402769|lt=Sakai Tadayoshi|1=Sakai Tadakiyo}}, an early Edo period hereditary daimyō, rōjū, and tairō (died {{ill|1681|en|1681|WD=Q7645|lt=1681|1=1681}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Eiroku|en|Eiroku|WD=Q1143341|lt=Eiroku|1=Eiroku}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1567|en|1567|WD=Q6642|lt=1567|1=1567}} {{ill|November 19|en|November 19|WD=Q3026|lt=November 19|1=November 19}}） – {{ill|Takeda Yoshinobu|en|Takeda Yoshinobu|WD=Q837273|lt=Takeda Yoshinobu|1=Takeda Yoshinobu}}, a military commander ({{ill|Busho (Rank)|ja|武将|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Busho (Rank)|1=military commander|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11545923}}) (born {{ill|1538|en|1538|WD=Q6470|lt=1538|1=1538}}).

